<think>I found out that the cultural environment affects international marketing activities in several ways. I will now provide the answer:</think>

<answer>The cultural environment affects international marketing activities by influencing consumer behaviour, communication, product adaptation, and marketing strategies. Marketers need to be aware of cultural differences, such as language, religion, values, aesthetics, customs, and manners, to adapt their marketing concepts and strategies accordingly. Ignoring cultural differences can lead to failure in implementing marketing programs and can damage a company's reputation. Understanding the cultural environment helps marketers gain a deeper understanding of the market and reduces the risk of investing money in unprofitable markets.</answer>